#  devops deployment project

## overview

this project demonstrates a complete end-to-end devops pipeline for deploying a node.js application on aws ec2 using modern production practices. the system automates build, packaging, deployment, health validation, and rollback to ensure safe and reliable releases without downtime.

instead of manually ssh into servers and restarting services, the entire deployment is triggered automatically on every push to the main branch through github actions.

the goal of this project is to simulate how real production systems deploy applications safely and consistently.

---

## problem statement

traditional deployments usually involve:

* manually logging into servers
* running npm install
* restarting processes
* risking downtime or broken releases

this approach is slow, error-prone, and unsafe.

to solve this, the project implements:

* automated ci cd pipeline
* artifact-based deployments
* health checks before traffic switch
* automatic rollback on failure
* zero downtime reloads

---

## architecture

high level flow:

developer push
→ github actions builds artifact
→ artifact copied to ec2
→ deploy script runs
→ health check validation
→ symlink switch
→ pm2 reload
→ nginx serves traffic

detailed architecture:

browser
↓
nginx reverse proxy (port 80)
↓
pm2 managed node application (port 5000)
↓
/opt/app/current → active release
↓
/opt/app/releases/v1, v2, v3

---

## tech stack

* node.js (backend api)
* nginx (reverse proxy)
* pm2 (process manager)
* github actions (ci cd)
* aws ec2 (hosting)
* bash scripting (automation)

---

## features implemented

* automated deployment on git push
* artifact-based packaging in ci pipeline
* versioned release directories
* symbolic link switching for active version
* health check endpoint validation
* automatic rollback on failure
* zero downtime deployments
* pm2 auto restart on crash
* pm2 auto start on reboot
* environment variable configuration
* nginx reverse proxy routing

---

## deployment strategy

### step 1 — build artifact

github actions installs dependencies and packages the application into a tar archive.

### step 2 — copy artifact

the artifact is securely transferred to the ec2 server.

### step 3 — release creation

deploy script extracts the artifact into a new versioned directory.

example:

```
/opt/app/releases/v1770818599
```

### step 4 — health check

the new version starts on a temporary port and the /health endpoint is validated.

### step 5 — traffic switch

if healthy, a symbolic link updates:

```
/opt/app/current → new version
```

### step 6 — reload

pm2 reloads the app without downtime.

### rollback behavior

if health check fails:

* new release is deleted
* symlink remains unchanged
* old version keeps running

users never experience downtime.

---

## project structure

```
backend/                  application source code
scripts/setup.sh          server provisioning script
scripts/deploy.sh         deployment automation script
.github/workflows/        ci cd pipeline
```

---

## how to run locally

```
cd backend
npm install
npm start
```

app runs on:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## how to deploy

push to main branch:

```
git push origin main
```

deployment happens automatically through github actions.

---

## verification commands (ec2)

check active version:

```
readlink -f /opt/app/current
```

check health:

```
curl localhost:5000/health
```

check version:

```
curl localhost:5000/version
```

check process:

```
pm2 status
```

